(42, 23, 31, 43, 15, 6, 6, 'what shall be done in the dry', 'Connection of Withering and Judgment', 'This connection highlights the theme of judgment on those who do not remain in a state of life or righteousness. Both passages emphasize the consequences of being ''withered'' or cast away, suggesting a parallel in the fate of those who do not abide in the source of life.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
